[8]An ancient legend says that saint Materne would have rather lived in the {the{the first century ad}} ad.
[9]It would have been the deceased son of the widow of Naim, resurrected by Jesus.
[10]Sent by saint Peter in the company of two disciples, Valère, and Eucher, in order to evangelize the north of Gaul and Germania, Materne would, therefore, always according to the legend, brought christianity to these regions as soon as the {{s}}, founding many places of worship and evangelizing a large number of cities, in particular in the region of the meuse.
